00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:13.709 align:middle line:84%
Leave me! Leave me! Leave me!

00:15:13.709 --> 00:15:17.810 align:middle line:84%
You heartless bandits!

00:15:17.810 --> 00:15:22.187 align:middle line:84%
Where's your chief?

00:15:22.187 --> 00:15:25.613 align:middle line:90%
What right have you to terrorise
women from good families?

00:15:25.613 --> 00:15:27.905 align:middle line:90%
Aren't you ashamed?
- Ashamed?

00:15:27.905 --> 00:15:31.155 align:middle line:90%
Shame is for good folks,
not for bandits and robbers.

00:15:31.155 --> 00:15:37.405 align:middle line:90%
As for me, my grandfather was a bandit,
my father was a bandit! But I wasn't.

00:15:37.405 --> 00:15:42.405 align:middle line:90%
And your husband went and made me one!
- My husband?

00:15:42.405 --> 00:15:46.448 align:middle line:90%
Who are you?
- Jagga. And I was innocent.

00:15:46.448 --> 00:15:51.822 align:middle line:90%
But without a shard of evidence,
your husband framed me...

00:15:51.822 --> 00:15:55.610 align:middle line:90%
just because my father, my grandfather
were bandits.

00:15:55.610 --> 00:15:59.501 align:middle line:90%
He framed me for rape
and he sent me to jail.

00:15:59.501 --> 00:16:07.905 align:middle line:90%
So I've decided to prove
your husband right.

00:16:07.905 --> 00:16:15.542 align:middle line:84%
Coward!

00:16:15.542 --> 00:16:19.516 align:middle line:84%
See what's wrong with her.

00:16:19.516 --> 00:16:22.670 align:middle line:84%
Has she come to her senses?

00:16:22.670 --> 00:16:27.277 align:middle line:84%
No, she's still in a swoon.

00:16:27.277 --> 00:16:32.779 align:middle line:90%
Let her go, Chief. She's pregnant.
She's going to become a mother.

00:16:32.779 --> 00:16:37.480 align:middle line:84%
Touch her, and you go to hell.

00:16:37.480 --> 00:16:43.279 align:middle line:84%
Pregnant? With a baby?

00:16:43.279 --> 00:16:50.818 align:middle line:90%
Her husband said that children born
of good folks turn out good.

00:16:50.818 --> 00:16:54.231 align:middle line:84%
And children born of bandits...

00:16:54.231 --> 00:16:58.482 align:middle line:84%
turn out to be bandits. Always.

00:16:58.482 --> 00:17:06.234 align:middle line:90%
Now let's see what the lawyer's son
turns out to be.

00:17:06.234 --> 00:17:11.284 align:middle line:84%
Send her back once she recovers.

00:17:11.284 --> 00:17:24.604 align:middle line:90%
Good are those born of good folks!
And of bandits are bandits born.

00:17:24.604 --> 00:17:27.558 align:middle line:90%
You should make me a gift.
- What's the occasion?

00:17:27.558 --> 00:17:30.965 align:middle line:90%
Not any occasion.
The lady is back.

00:17:30.965 --> 00:17:34.558 align:middle line:84%
What did you say? The lady?

00:17:34.558 --> 00:17:37.501 align:middle line:84%
Leela!

00:17:37.501 --> 00:17:42.225 align:middle line:84%
Leela!

00:17:42.225 --> 00:17:44.101 align:middle line:84%
Why is it dark in here?

00:17:44.101 --> 00:17:45.850 align:middle line:84%
Nathu! Bansi! Naina!

00:17:45.850 --> 00:17:51.472 align:middle line:84%
Lights! Tonight we celebrate!

00:17:51.472 --> 00:17:52.808 align:middle line:84%
Leela.

00:17:52.808 --> 00:17:57.725 align:middle line:84%
It is you who lights up my life.

00:17:57.725 --> 00:18:06.973 align:middle line:84%
Leela.

00:18:06.973 --> 00:18:10.791 align:middle line:90%
Now that you're back,
even the lights seem so bright!

00:18:10.791 --> 00:18:19.809 align:middle line:84%
Give me the wick.

00:18:19.809 --> 00:18:26.987 align:middle line:90%
But Leela, how did you escape?
I hope you weren't in danger?

00:18:26.987 --> 00:18:33.682 align:middle line:90%
Your love was with me.
How could anyone even look up at me?

00:18:33.682 --> 00:18:44.581 align:middle line:90%
You are tired. Change.
I'll bring you your dressing gown.

00:18:44.581 --> 00:18:51.162 align:middle line:84%
These last four days.

00:18:51.162 --> 00:18:55.922 align:middle line:90%
The last four days were
like a lifetime.

00:18:55.922 --> 00:18:58.695 align:middle line:90%
I took the police and I looked
everywhere for you.

00:18:58.695 --> 00:19:11.125 align:middle line:84%
All the while, I feared...

00:19:11.125 --> 00:19:22.554 align:middle line:84%
I feared you were in grave danger!

00:19:22.554 --> 00:19:28.262 align:middle line:90%
But how did you escape?
And who was this bandit?

00:19:28.262 --> 00:19:32.493 align:middle line:90%
Some Jagga.
He said that you had convicted him.

00:19:32.493 --> 00:19:35.350 align:middle line:84%
Jagga.

00:19:35.350 --> 00:19:41.748 align:middle line:90%
So he escaped to get even with me!
If he has done anything to you...

00:19:41.748 --> 00:19:46.429 align:middle line:90%
I'll see to it that he hangs!
- At heart, he's a devil.

00:19:46.429 --> 00:19:51.409 align:middle line:90%
But God saved me at the last moment.
Thank God!

00:19:51.409 --> 00:19:55.319 align:middle line:84%
Tell me something.

00:19:55.319 --> 00:19:57.120 align:middle line:84%
Ask.

00:19:57.120 --> 00:20:02.652 align:middle line:90%
Does a bandit's son necessarily
become a bandit?

00:20:02.652 --> 00:20:08.264 align:middle line:84%
Yes, it's bound to happen.

00:20:08.264 --> 00:20:22.503 align:middle line:90%
But why do you ask?
- Just like that.

00:20:22.503 --> 00:20:27.419 align:middle line:90%
Let's see what comes first.
Your becoming a magistrate, or...

00:20:27.419 --> 00:20:31.782 align:middle line:84%
Why? Is someone expected?

00:20:31.782 --> 00:20:34.211 align:middle line:84%
A new guest.

00:20:34.211 --> 00:20:39.137 align:middle line:90%
Now I don't have any chances
of becoming a magistrate.

00:20:39.137 --> 00:20:42.503 align:middle line:84%
Why? What happened?

00:20:42.503 --> 00:20:52.753 align:middle line:90%
Whatever...
let's talk of something else.

00:20:52.753 --> 00:20:56.440 align:middle line:84%
How do you like this?

00:20:56.440 --> 00:20:58.306 align:middle line:84%
Nice.

00:20:58.306 --> 00:21:00.566 align:middle line:84%
Nice.

00:21:00.566 --> 00:21:07.378 align:middle line:90%
Listen...
Are you annoyed with me?

00:21:07.378 --> 00:21:11.336 align:middle line:84%
Annoyed? No.

00:21:11.336 --> 00:21:17.211 align:middle line:84%
Why should I be annoyed with you?

00:21:17.211 --> 00:21:28.285 align:middle line:84%
Have my lunch sent over.

00:21:28.285 --> 00:21:30.160 align:middle line:90%
What's the matter?
Where are the servants?

00:21:30.160 --> 00:21:34.196 align:middle line:90%
God knows! Maybe they're all dead!
I have to do all the chores.

00:21:34.196 --> 00:21:36.655 align:middle line:90%
Let me help you.
- You'd rather tell her all this.

00:21:36.655 --> 00:21:40.363 align:middle line:84%
She's sitting around like a queen!

00:21:40.363 --> 00:21:44.815 align:middle line:90%
Not to be cross with Leela.
I told her not to strain herself.

00:21:44.815 --> 00:21:49.160 align:middle line:90%
You know the condition she is in.
And in a few days from now...

00:21:49.160 --> 00:21:54.613 align:middle line:90%
She's going to bear the fruit
of her sins!

00:21:54.613 --> 00:21:58.280 align:middle line:90%
What are you saying?!
- What everyone else is saying!

00:21:58.280 --> 00:22:03.239 align:middle line:90%
For four days, she lived with a bandit!
And Jagga that!

00:22:03.239 --> 00:22:07.363 align:middle line:90%
Don't you remember what
he was convicted for?

00:22:07.363 --> 00:22:10.405 align:middle line:90%
Do you enjoy making someone unhappy?
The jaundiced eye sees all yellow.

00:22:10.405 --> 00:22:13.680 align:middle line:90%
Do you think you're beyond scrutiny?
Don't you forget...

00:22:13.680 --> 00:22:16.193 align:middle line:90%
women have had to stand the test of
chastity. Because society asks for it.

00:22:16.193 --> 00:22:22.330 align:middle line:84%
Bhabhi! (Sister-in-law)

00:22:22.330 --> 00:22:25.242 align:middle line:90%
Forgive me Bhabhi,
your pot is broken.

00:22:25.242 --> 00:22:29.860 align:middle line:90%
It's only an earthen pot. But remember,
a woman's honour is far more fragile.

00:22:29.860 --> 00:23:00.259 align:middle line:90%
Once disgraced, her honour
can never be redeemed.

00:23:00.259 --> 00:23:03.789 align:middle line:84%
Just answer my question!

00:23:03.789 --> 00:23:07.200 align:middle line:90%
Did you not know that your wife
was seeing her lover on the sly?

00:23:07.200 --> 00:23:11.300 align:middle line:90%
The villagers used to say that.
But I didn't heed what they said.

00:23:11.300 --> 00:23:14.295 align:middle line:90%
You haven't yet told the court
why your wife deserted you.

00:23:14.295 --> 00:23:29.296 align:middle line:90%
You know it! Women are adulterous!
- I know what that means!

00:23:29.296 --> 00:23:34.186 align:middle line:90%
Raghu, how can you lose
your cool in court?

00:23:34.186 --> 00:23:39.307 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid your chances of
magistrate ship may be clouded.

00:23:39.307 --> 00:23:47.878 align:middle line:90%
Chances of a magistrate ship?
That's out of question now.

00:23:47.878 --> 00:23:52.690 align:middle line:90%
Can a lawyer whose wife is under
suspicion ever become a magistrate?

00:23:52.690 --> 00:23:53.823 align:middle line:84%
Raghu!

00:23:53.823 --> 00:23:57.352 align:middle line:90%
The whole town is agog!
- What are you saying?

00:23:57.352 --> 00:24:01.364 align:middle line:90%
Aren't you ashamed to talk like this
about your wife?

00:24:01.364 --> 00:24:04.391 align:middle line:84%
I'm just saying what everyone is saying.

00:24:04.391 --> 00:24:08.281 align:middle line:84%
Let them say what they want.

00:24:08.281 --> 00:24:14.230 align:middle line:84%
You're right. That's what I decided.

00:24:14.230 --> 00:24:17.129 align:middle line:84%
Let them say what they want.

00:24:17.129 --> 00:24:23.318 align:middle line:90%
But how do I get rid of the suspicion?
It's like a leech sucking on...

00:24:23.318 --> 00:24:45.465 align:middle line:90%
some dark corner of my mind!
- What now?

00:24:45.465 --> 00:24:50.314 align:middle line:84%
Nathu! Naina! Bhabhi!

00:24:50.314 --> 00:24:53.903 align:middle line:84%
Where's everyone?

00:24:53.903 --> 00:24:59.138 align:middle line:84%
Send Bhabhi over to me.

00:24:59.138 --> 00:25:02.979 align:middle line:84%
I am scared.

00:25:02.979 --> 00:25:06.780 align:middle line:84%
Why isn't someone coming to me?

00:25:06.780 --> 00:25:15.337 align:middle line:90%
That's my husband.
Please, send him over to me.

00:25:15.337 --> 00:25:18.645 align:middle line:84%
Look Raghu...

00:25:18.645 --> 00:25:21.346 align:middle line:90%
I'm telling you again! That baby
isn't going to be born in this house

00:25:21.346 --> 00:25:24.593 align:middle line:90%
If she wants to have her bastard,
let her go elsewhere.

00:25:24.593 --> 00:25:27.223 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to let the honour
of my family be tainted.

00:25:27.223 --> 00:25:30.131 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to throw this
wanton woman out!

00:25:30.131 --> 00:25:34.288 align:middle line:90%
No! I'm not going anywhere!
No one can take me away from here!

00:25:34.288 --> 00:25:45.698 align:middle line:90%
He knows that I'm innocent!
He trusts me, he trusts me!

00:25:45.698 --> 00:25:50.379 align:middle line:84%
You're here! Now I'm afraid of no one!

00:25:50.379 --> 00:25:54.173 align:middle line:90%
Have you heard?
They want to throw me out!

00:25:54.173 --> 00:26:00.296 align:middle line:90%
They say I'm a wanton woman!
They say, I've no right to be here!

00:26:00.296 --> 00:26:05.575 align:middle line:90%
But now you're here.
No one will dare anymore.

00:26:05.575 --> 00:26:12.669 align:middle line:90%
Tell them I'm untainted!
Tell them you trust me.

00:26:12.669 --> 00:26:34.708 align:middle line:84%
Tell them I'm mothering your child.

00:26:34.708 --> 00:26:38.970 align:middle line:84%
Have you fallen for what they say?

00:26:38.970 --> 00:26:44.130 align:middle line:90%
You're the one who told me...
I don't care for the barking dogs.

00:26:44.130 --> 00:26:50.269 align:middle line:90%
If you desert me, who else
in this world can I turn to?

00:26:50.269 --> 00:26:55.668 align:middle line:84%
Tell me... tell me that you trust me!

00:26:55.668 --> 00:26:57.885 align:middle line:84%
Do you think you're above scrutiny?

00:26:57.885 --> 00:27:15.536 align:middle line:90%
Don't you forget women have
had to stand the test of chastity.

00:27:15.536 --> 00:27:21.449 align:middle line:90%
Why are you quiet?
Speak... speak!

00:27:21.449 --> 00:27:28.444 align:middle line:90%
You can see the state I'm in.
I'm afraid... afraid!

00:27:28.444 --> 00:27:35.163 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to become a mother
...the mother of your child.

00:27:35.163 --> 00:27:41.199 align:middle line:90%
Have mercy! This is your baby.
This baby is yours!

00:27:41.199 --> 00:27:58.266 align:middle line:90%
Get out!
Get out of here!

00:27:58.266 --> 00:28:08.598 align:middle line:84%
"A dutiful wife like Sita."

00:28:08.598 --> 00:28:14.801 align:middle line:84%
"You gave exile to her."

00:28:14.801 --> 00:28:25.610 align:middle line:84%
"Why didn't the earth rip apart?"

00:28:25.610 --> 00:28:30.955 align:middle line:84%
"Why didn't the sky rip apart?"

00:28:30.955 --> 00:28:35.202 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:28:35.202 --> 00:28:39.852 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:28:39.852 --> 00:28:43.461 align:middle line:84%
"The dear one of Lord Rama."

00:28:43.461 --> 00:28:47.464 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:28:47.464 --> 00:28:51.381 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:28:51.381 --> 00:28:55.381 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:28:55.381 --> 00:28:59.857 align:middle line:84%
"Women have to endure injustice."

00:28:59.857 --> 00:29:03.985 align:middle line:84%
"Look, the King of the palace."

00:29:03.985 --> 00:29:07.131 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:29:07.131 --> 00:29:21.690 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:29:21.690 --> 00:29:25.928 align:middle line:84%
"Look, the King of the palace."

00:29:25.928 --> 00:29:28.941 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:29:28.941 --> 00:29:32.765 align:middle line:84%
"What a game is he playing!"

00:29:32.765 --> 00:29:36.964 align:middle line:90%
"From the shell, a pearl,
and in the muck."

00:29:36.964 --> 00:29:40.698 align:middle line:84%
"The beautiful lotus is blossoming."

00:29:40.698 --> 00:29:48.890 align:middle line:84%
"The beautiful lotus is blossoming."

00:29:48.890 --> 00:29:52.169 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:29:52.169 --> 00:29:56.735 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:29:56.735 --> 00:30:00.113 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:00.113 --> 00:30:05.561 align:middle line:90%
"Congratulations, Lawyer!
A son has born to you."

00:30:05.561 --> 00:30:12.412 align:middle line:90%
Son of a decent family!
Born in a filthy gutter!

00:30:12.412 --> 00:30:15.780 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:15.780 --> 00:30:19.616 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:19.616 --> 00:30:23.158 align:middle line:84%
"Lord, Your ways are strange."

00:30:23.158 --> 00:30:25.533 align:middle line:90%
Do you not know what your wife
and your son went through...

00:30:25.533 --> 00:30:28.998 align:middle line:90%
after you shut your doors on them?
- No

00:30:28.998 --> 00:30:32.296 align:middle line:84%
Nor did you try to find out.

00:30:32.296 --> 00:30:35.322 align:middle line:84%
But I can tell you.

00:30:35.322 --> 00:30:40.316 align:middle line:90%
To get out of your way,
your wife left Lucknow.

00:30:40.316 --> 00:30:46.108 align:middle line:90%
And your innocent son grew up
in a Bombay slum.

00:30:46.108 --> 00:30:57.274 align:middle line:84%
One day...

00:30:57.274 --> 00:31:05.350 align:middle line:84%
Police! Scram!

00:31:05.350 --> 00:31:11.511 align:middle line:84%
Greetings, sir.

00:31:11.511 --> 00:31:15.205 align:middle line:90%
Hey Nathu...
- Hello, Constable.

00:31:15.205 --> 00:31:18.355 align:middle line:90%
What are you up there like a monkey?
Why don't you go to school?

00:31:18.355 --> 00:31:22.878 align:middle line:84%
At school, the master asks for fees.

00:31:22.878 --> 00:31:27.830 align:middle line:90%
My father hasn't the money
to send me to school.

00:31:27.830 --> 00:31:30.241 align:middle line:90%
Look at Leela's son, Raj.
He lives in this slum too.

00:31:30.241 --> 00:31:35.748 align:middle line:90%
His mother is worse off. Yet she
sends her boy to such a big school.

00:31:35.748 --> 00:31:42.229 align:middle line:90%
What did you say? He isn't a boy.
He's a sissy!

00:31:42.229 --> 00:31:47.624 align:middle line:90%
Ma, why do you put oil in my hair?
- Oil keeps the hair soft.

00:31:47.624 --> 00:31:50.325 align:middle line:90%
But why do boys in the
neighbourhood call me sissy?

00:31:50.325 --> 00:31:54.161 align:middle line:90%
So what?
How do they compare with you?

00:31:54.161 --> 00:31:56.809 align:middle line:90%
You're a good boy
who goes to school.

00:31:56.809 --> 00:31:59.299 align:middle line:90%
You'll grow up to become
an educated man.

00:31:59.299 --> 00:32:03.650 align:middle line:84%
And those vagabonds will go to jail.

00:32:03.650 --> 00:32:06.760 align:middle line:84%
Mother, who are called vagabonds?

00:32:06.760 --> 00:32:09.733 align:middle line:84%
The ones who just tramp around.

00:32:09.733 --> 00:32:12.266 align:middle line:90%
Those who think that whatever
belongs to others, belongs to them.

00:32:12.266 --> 00:32:16.304 align:middle line:90%
Those who gamble and drink
instead of going to school.

00:32:16.304 --> 00:32:19.230 align:middle line:84%
And they have fun!

00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:21.874 align:middle line:90%
Ma, when I grow up,
I'll become vagabond too.

00:32:21.874 --> 00:32:28.976 align:middle line:84%
Nonsense! You'll become a lawyer.

00:32:28.976 --> 00:32:31.360 align:middle line:84%
Then a magistrate.

00:32:31.360 --> 00:32:32.900 align:middle line:84%
And then, a judge.

00:32:32.900 --> 00:32:35.265 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

00:32:35.265 --> 00:32:38.279 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

00:32:38.279 --> 00:32:42.788 align:middle line:90%
You're sitting here?
Everyone's out there buying chocolates.

00:32:42.788 --> 00:32:44.847 align:middle line:84%
I don't have money

00:32:44.847 --> 00:32:47.386 align:middle line:90%
Why, doesn't your mother
give you money?

00:32:47.386 --> 00:32:50.399 align:middle line:84%
Daddy gives me a whole Rupee every day!

00:32:50.399 --> 00:32:52.763 align:middle line:84%
You're rich. And I'm poor.

00:32:52.763 --> 00:32:55.452 align:middle line:90%
Eat this
- No.

00:32:55.452 --> 00:32:57.472 align:middle line:90%
Ma says never ask
for anything to eat.

00:32:57.472 --> 00:33:03.940 align:middle line:90%
If she told you not to ask,
go ahead and snatch it.

00:33:03.940 --> 00:33:04.453 align:middle line:84%
Wild!

00:33:04.453 --> 00:33:07.957 align:middle line:90%
Wild?
- No, no, no.

00:33:07.957 --> 00:33:10.552 align:middle line:90%
You're coming to my place
this evening, aren't you?

00:33:10.552 --> 00:33:13.518 align:middle line:90%
Why, what's happening?
- My birthday party!

00:33:13.518 --> 00:33:15.254 align:middle line:84%
You must come! It's going to be fun!

00:33:15.254 --> 00:33:20.136 align:middle line:90%
You know, Daddy has ordered
such a huge cake!

00:33:20.136 --> 00:33:23.552 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday to you!

00:33:23.552 --> 00:33:32.706 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday to you!

00:33:32.706 --> 00:33:34.799 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday to you!

00:33:34.799 --> 00:33:36.997 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

00:33:36.997 --> 00:33:49.176 align:middle line:84%
Let's go and eat ice cream.

00:33:49.176 --> 00:33:53.259 align:middle line:84%
Raj, aren't you giving me a gift?

00:33:53.259 --> 00:33:57.509 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have money to buy anything.
I'll give you some other time.

00:33:57.509 --> 00:34:01.704 align:middle line:90%
Must you only buy something
to make a gift?

00:34:01.704 --> 00:34:12.402 align:middle line:90%
You can give me a flower.
- Really?

00:34:12.402 --> 00:34:14.734 align:middle line:84%
Here you are.

00:34:14.734 --> 00:34:18.670 align:middle line:90%
Someday, I'm going to make
lots of money.

00:34:18.670 --> 00:34:22.275 align:middle line:90%
And I'll buy a gift for you.
Something better than all this.

00:34:22.275 --> 00:34:24.192 align:middle line:84%
Do that.

00:34:24.192 --> 00:34:26.688 align:middle line:90%
But can anything be better
than this flower?

00:34:26.688 --> 00:34:30.109 align:middle line:90%
Ritu! Ritu! Your father
is calling you! - Coming!

00:34:30.109 --> 00:34:39.920 align:middle line:84%
Come on Raj, meet my father.

00:34:39.920 --> 00:34:42.250 align:middle line:84%
You always say this.

00:34:42.250 --> 00:34:44.734 align:middle line:84%
Ritu, say hello to the Judge"

00:34:44.734 --> 00:34:47.161 align:middle line:84%
Hello, Judge.

00:34:47.161 --> 00:34:49.237 align:middle line:84%
Bless you.

00:34:49.237 --> 00:34:55.283 align:middle line:90%
You've grown up in these four years
You must've forgotten me.

00:34:55.283 --> 00:34:57.594 align:middle line:84%
Happy birthday

00:34:57.594 --> 00:35:03.816 align:middle line:90%
I've just arrived from Lucknow.
I owe you a present.

00:35:03.816 --> 00:35:09.158 align:middle line:84%
As of now, I can give you a flower.

00:35:09.158 --> 00:35:15.887 align:middle line:84%
Here you are.

00:35:15.887 --> 00:35:19.532 align:middle line:84%
Let me put it on your hair.

00:35:19.532 --> 00:35:22.143 align:middle line:90%
Someone has already put a flower
over there.

00:35:22.143 --> 00:35:24.705 align:middle line:84%
Raj has given me this flower

00:35:24.705 --> 00:35:28.356 align:middle line:90%
Daddy, this is Raj.
He's in my class.

00:35:28.356 --> 00:35:30.540 align:middle line:90%
I see.
- Hello.

00:35:30.540 --> 00:35:34.221 align:middle line:90%
Hello.
- Hello.

00:35:34.221 --> 00:35:37.224 align:middle line:84%
God bless you, son"

00:35:37.224 --> 00:35:40.730 align:middle line:90%
Raj says that he will become a judge
when he grows up.

00:35:40.730 --> 00:35:44.136 align:middle line:84%
Very good!

00:35:44.136 --> 00:35:48.120 align:middle line:84%
Your father must be a real gentleman.

00:35:48.120 --> 00:35:49.563 align:middle line:84%
What does your father do?

00:35:49.563 --> 00:35:54.968 align:middle line:90%
I don't have my father.
I have only my mother

00:35:54.968 --> 00:35:57.851 align:middle line:90%
Has he passed away?
- No! Don't say that!

00:35:57.851 --> 00:36:03.523 align:middle line:90%
My mother says he is alive.
But...

00:36:03.523 --> 00:36:08.716 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't live with you
...and you haven't seen him either?

00:36:08.716 --> 00:36:12.795 align:middle line:90%
Your father is a strange man.
- Not a word about my father.

00:36:12.795 --> 00:36:16.724 align:middle line:84%
Else... else...

00:36:16.724 --> 00:36:21.657 align:middle line:90%
Raj!
- Rita!

00:36:21.657 --> 00:36:26.472 align:middle line:90%
How can you let your daughter
play with boys like him?

00:36:26.472 --> 00:36:28.781 align:middle line:84%
Go to play, Ritu"

00:36:28.781 --> 00:36:33.753 align:middle line:90%
Why, what's wrong with the boy?
I like him.

00:36:33.753 --> 00:36:38.546 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't even know his father's
name, and you like him?

00:36:38.546 --> 00:36:40.940 align:middle line:90%
I'd say he's just a wastrel
- Forget it.

00:36:40.940 --> 00:36:44.958 align:middle line:90%
Must you hang on to
those rotten old ideas?

00:36:44.958 --> 00:36:47.619 align:middle line:84%
What was the Bandit's name?

00:36:47.619 --> 00:36:49.329 align:middle line:84%
Yes, Jagga.

00:36:49.329 --> 00:36:53.265 align:middle line:90%
I remember you saying the same
at his trial.

00:36:53.265 --> 00:36:57.653 align:middle line:90%
That a bandit's son
always becomes a bandit.

00:36:57.653 --> 00:36:59.240 align:middle line:84%
I still stand by that principle.

00:36:59.240 --> 00:37:04.482 align:middle line:90%
Principles, principles and principles!
It's because of these blind dogmas...

00:37:04.482 --> 00:37:07.357 align:middle line:90%
that you lost someone
as precious as Leela.

00:37:07.357 --> 00:37:10.155 align:middle line:90%
And because of your principles,
you never married again.

00:37:10.155 --> 00:37:13.198 align:middle line:90%
The dry parched desert that
your life is, is your own doing.

00:37:13.198 --> 00:37:14.604 align:middle line:90%
So much so that you would rather
destroy a friendship...

00:37:14.604 --> 00:37:17.395 align:middle line:90%
between two innocent children?
Why, what has the poor child done...

00:37:17.395 --> 00:37:21.221 align:middle line:84%
to bring you to harm?

00:37:21.221 --> 00:37:23.178 align:middle line:84%
Not this boy. But it was...

00:37:23.178 --> 00:37:29.615 align:middle line:90%
someone like him who destroyed my life
...and brought me to disgrace.

00:37:29.615 --> 00:37:32.448 align:middle line:90%
Maybe today, he too says
what this boy just said...

00:37:32.448 --> 00:37:38.326 align:middle line:90%
I'm only my mother's son
...I have no father.

00:37:38.326 --> 00:37:43.240 align:middle line:84%
In every urchin I see him...

00:37:43.240 --> 00:37:46.586 align:middle line:90%
the one whom my wife bore,
the one who isn't mine.

00:37:46.586 --> 00:37:51.876 align:middle line:84%
My wife's, yet not mine.

00:37:51.876 --> 00:37:54.278 align:middle line:90%
Rita looks good in that photo,
doesn't she?

00:37:54.278 --> 00:37:57.943 align:middle line:90%
But Ma, why do you work so hard?
This is why you fall ill.

00:37:57.943 --> 00:38:00.859 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to let you work
anymore, you understand?

00:38:00.859 --> 00:38:04.985 align:middle line:90%
You mad boy! If I don't work,
how are we going to eat?

00:38:04.985 --> 00:38:07.517 align:middle line:90%
I'm a man. I'm the one
who is going to work.

00:38:07.517 --> 00:38:09.699 align:middle line:84%
From tomorrow, no going to school!

00:38:09.699 --> 00:38:13.963 align:middle line:90%
You won't go to school?
Won't you?

00:38:13.963 --> 00:38:16.212 align:middle line:90%
How will you become a gentleman,
unless you educate yourself?

00:38:16.212 --> 00:38:20.700 align:middle line:90%
You want to be a vagabond!
- Mother!

00:38:20.700 --> 00:38:25.959 align:middle line:90%
Without schooling, how can you become
a lawyer, a magistrate, a judge?

00:38:25.959 --> 00:38:34.131 align:middle line:90%
If you say so, I'll go to school
...and I'll work too.

00:38:34.131 --> 00:38:38.900 align:middle line:90%
But I won't become a judge.
At Rita's I met a judge.

00:38:38.900 --> 00:39:02.480 align:middle line:84%
I didn't like him.

00:39:02.480 --> 00:39:10.476 align:middle line:90%
"Go for a stroll, those
who are going."

00:39:10.476 --> 00:39:15.170 align:middle line:90%
"Go for a stroll, those
who are going."

00:39:15.170 --> 00:39:18.445 align:middle line:84%
"Since when we have been waiting,

00:39:18.445 --> 00:39:23.508 align:middle line:84%
we cobblers."

00:39:23.508 --> 00:39:28.633 align:middle line:84%
Page 120.

00:39:28.633 --> 00:39:29.938 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

00:39:29.938 --> 00:39:32.642 align:middle line:90%
Good morning, teacher.
Sorry, I'm late.

00:39:32.642 --> 00:39:36.300 align:middle line:90%
I work, you know. I work
- What's all this?

00:39:36.300 --> 00:39:41.716 align:middle line:84%
Brush, wax... I give you a good polish.

00:39:41.716 --> 00:39:44.767 align:middle line:90%
Your name has been struck
from the rolls.

00:39:44.767 --> 00:39:47.500 align:middle line:90%
What?
- You can't study here anymore.

00:39:47.500 --> 00:39:52.666 align:middle line:90%
But I've brought the fees too! If you
say so, I'll stop polishing boots.

00:39:52.666 --> 00:40:01.215 align:middle line:84%
Silence!

00:40:01.215 --> 00:40:04.220 align:middle line:84%
So I can't study here any longer, can I?

00:40:04.220 --> 00:40:06.361 align:middle line:84%
No.

00:40:06.361 --> 00:40:12.730 align:middle line:90%
For a minute, can I talk to Rita?
I have a gift for her.

00:40:12.730 --> 00:40:28.512 align:middle line:90%
