- Out of here. Get out.

02:15:59.371 --> 02:16:03.954 align:middle line:90%
Before I leave, I'd like
to ask you a question.

02:16:03.954 --> 02:16:08.781 align:middle line:90%
What if it was your son in my place?
And because he's poor...

02:16:08.781 --> 02:16:15.893 align:middle line:90%
..because he was brought up in the slums
and was forced into crime...

02:16:15.893 --> 02:16:19.310 align:middle line:90%
...what if it was he who was being
denied his love, his life?

02:16:19.310 --> 02:16:33.655 align:middle line:84%
How would you have felt?

02:16:33.655 --> 02:16:38.538 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

02:16:38.538 --> 02:16:40.450 align:middle line:84%
Raj! Raj!

02:16:40.450 --> 02:16:43.370 align:middle line:84%
Jagga has called you.

02:16:43.370 --> 02:17:21.977 align:middle line:90%
There's a big heist.
A bank is to be looted.

02:17:21.977 --> 02:17:25.664 align:middle line:84%
Open the door!

02:17:25.664 --> 02:17:28.330 align:middle line:90%
Open up.
- Who is it?

02:17:28.330 --> 02:17:31.144 align:middle line:84%
Open up!

02:17:31.144 --> 02:17:36.563 align:middle line:84%
Open the door!

02:17:36.563 --> 02:17:45.900 align:middle line:90%
Who is there?
- Open the door!

02:17:45.900 --> 02:17:48.948 align:middle line:84%
Who are you?

02:17:48.948 --> 02:17:52.755 align:middle line:84%
Don't you know me?

02:17:52.755 --> 02:17:56.441 align:middle line:84%
I'm Jagga.

02:17:56.441 --> 02:17:58.775 align:middle line:84%
Jagga!

02:17:58.775 --> 02:18:03.316 align:middle line:90%
The bandit?
- You could say so.

02:18:03.316 --> 02:18:08.775 align:middle line:90%
What do you want here?
- Silence!

02:18:08.775 --> 02:18:14.188 align:middle line:90%
The police are after me.
Where's Raj?

02:18:14.188 --> 02:18:23.150 align:middle line:90%
Get out of my house! I will do nothing
to help someone like you!

02:18:23.150 --> 02:18:30.310 align:middle line:90%
I had you once, and I let you go
Remember the day?

02:18:30.310 --> 02:18:35.975 align:middle line:90%
For twelve years, I cared for your son.
I made his life! For this day?

02:18:35.975 --> 02:18:40.787 align:middle line:90%
Made my son's life?
You forced him into crime.

02:18:40.787 --> 02:18:44.980 align:middle line:90%
Get out of my house. I don't want
your cursed shadow upon my son!

02:18:44.980 --> 02:18:47.609 align:middle line:84%
Get out! Get out of my house!

02:18:47.609 --> 02:18:53.984 align:middle line:84%
Police! Police!

02:18:53.984 --> 02:18:56.941 align:middle line:90%
Go on! Call the police!
- Police!

02:18:56.941 --> 02:19:01.236 align:middle line:90%
Let me see who saves you!
Scream!

02:19:01.236 --> 02:19:07.947 align:middle line:84%
Jagga!

02:19:07.947 --> 02:19:16.584 align:middle line:90%
Will you challenge your boss?
- You're no boss. You're Satan!

02:19:16.584 --> 02:19:28.281 align:middle line:84%
Satan!

02:19:28.281 --> 02:19:55.518 align:middle line:84%
Let's hear what you have to say now.

02:19:55.518 --> 02:19:59.679 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

02:19:59.679 --> 02:20:06.769 align:middle line:84%
Raj! No! No! Mercy!

02:20:06.769 --> 02:20:09.893 align:middle line:84%
No! Enough!

02:20:09.893 --> 02:20:44.856 align:middle line:84%
Jagga!

02:20:44.856 --> 02:21:05.849 align:middle line:90%
What have you done Raj?
- For my sins, this is atonement!

02:21:05.849 --> 02:21:23.885 align:middle line:84%
Police!

02:21:23.885 --> 02:21:33.324 align:middle line:84%
The accused may be presented.

02:21:33.324 --> 02:21:43.522 align:middle line:90%
What's the name of the accused?
- Sir, his name is Raj.

02:21:43.522 --> 02:21:50.420 align:middle line:90%
Father's name?
- Not known, sir. Maybe he has none.

02:21:50.420 --> 02:21:53.315 align:middle line:84%
Order!

02:21:53.315 --> 02:21:59.667 align:middle line:90%
Raj, you have been accused
of killing Jagga.

02:21:59.667 --> 02:22:05.102 align:middle line:90%
Do you have anything to say
in your defence?

02:22:05.102 --> 02:22:13.856 align:middle line:90%
Have you not appointed a lawyer
to defend yourself?

02:22:13.856 --> 02:22:19.505 align:middle line:90%
The case is adjourned. The government
will appoint a counsel for the defence.

02:22:19.505 --> 02:22:25.487 align:middle line:90%
I know the law. Raj killed
in self-defence. That's no crime.

02:22:25.487 --> 02:22:29.490 align:middle line:84%
Please save my Raj, somehow.

02:22:29.490 --> 02:22:33.132 align:middle line:90%
Your deposition is very important.
The whole case hinges on it.

02:22:33.132 --> 02:22:55.912 align:middle line:90%
Come to the court tomorrow.
- All right. Okay, dear.

02:22:55.912 --> 02:23:02.787 align:middle line:84%
Husband!

02:23:02.787 --> 02:23:04.135 align:middle line:84%
She is unconscious.

02:23:04.135 --> 02:23:08.305 align:middle line:84%
Move back! Move! Move!

02:23:08.305 --> 02:23:13.707 align:middle line:90%
Is she dead?
- She has been hurt on the head.

02:23:13.707 --> 02:23:22.662 align:middle line:90%
And Raj killed Jagga
to save my life.

02:23:22.662 --> 02:23:28.813 align:middle line:90%
Please sign here. This deposition
will surely save Raj.

02:23:28.813 --> 02:23:34.870 align:middle line:90%
If Raj is saved, I will be able
to die in peace.

02:23:34.870 --> 02:23:49.829 align:middle line:84%
I should be leaving now.

02:23:49.829 --> 02:23:51.617 align:middle line:84%
Mother!

02:23:51.617 --> 02:23:53.537 align:middle line:90%
My son!
- What happened to you, Ma?

02:23:53.537 --> 02:23:54.745 align:middle line:84%
My son!

02:23:54.745 --> 02:23:59.245 align:middle line:90%
That heartless judge has killed you!
What is his enmity with us?

02:23:59.245 --> 02:24:01.656 align:middle line:90%
You mustn't blame him, son.
- Why not?

02:24:01.656 --> 02:24:03.459 align:middle line:90%
He has always been tying
to make us miserable.

02:24:03.459 --> 02:24:08.887 align:middle line:84%
No son! He is your father.

02:24:08.887 --> 02:24:11.103 align:middle line:84%
My father?

02:24:11.103 --> 02:24:16.135 align:middle line:90%
What are you saying, Ma?
What has come over you?

02:24:16.135 --> 02:24:21.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm not out of my mind, son.
What I'm saying is the truth.

02:24:21.900 --> 02:24:24.746 align:middle line:90%
I could not bring myself
to tell you this until now.

02:24:24.746 --> 02:24:31.106 align:middle line:90%
But if not today, once I'm gone
who else could tell you?

02:24:31.106 --> 02:24:35.518 align:middle line:90%
This can't be, Ma!
This can never be!

02:24:35.518 --> 02:24:41.597 align:middle line:90%
This is a long story.
But I don't have the time.

02:24:41.597 --> 02:24:47.850 align:middle line:84%
Keep this. I'm leaving.

02:24:47.850 --> 02:24:51.950 align:middle line:90%
He will surely recognise you
when you show him this.

02:24:51.950 --> 02:24:56.684 align:middle line:84%
He has never forgiven me.

02:24:56.684 --> 02:25:03.536 align:middle line:84%
But he will surely forgive his son.

02:25:03.536 --> 02:25:07.510 align:middle line:90%
I won't seek mercy from the one
who tortured my mother all her life...

02:25:07.510 --> 02:25:14.198 align:middle line:90%
..the one who made her beg from door
to door. I won't have his mercy!

02:25:14.198 --> 02:25:16.943 align:middle line:84%
Ma, I won't have his mercy!

02:25:16.943 --> 02:25:23.118 align:middle line:90%
If I could see him for
once before I died...

02:25:23.118 --> 02:25:25.414 align:middle line:84%
But why would he come here.

02:25:25.414 --> 02:25:29.177 align:middle line:90%
Come.
- I'm leaving Ma.

02:25:29.177 --> 02:25:30.340 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:25:30.340 --> 02:25:32.927 align:middle line:90%
I'll avenge you, I will.
- No!

02:25:32.927 --> 02:25:35.751 align:middle line:90%
I'll surely avenge you, I will.
- No, son!.

02:25:35.751 --> 02:25:45.520 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:25:45.520 --> 02:25:48.552 align:middle line:84%
The Judge is here to see you.

02:25:48.552 --> 02:26:00.680 align:middle line:90%
Which Judge?
- The one whose car ran you over.

02:26:00.680 --> 02:26:05.639 align:middle line:84%
So he has come... before I'm dead.

02:26:05.639 --> 02:26:09.360 align:middle line:84%
Alas, I cannot see.

02:26:09.360 --> 02:26:15.316 align:middle line:84%
Nurse, give him my greetings.

02:26:15.316 --> 02:26:21.219 align:middle line:90%
I am ashamed about the accident.
Please forgive me.

02:26:21.219 --> 02:26:32.300 align:middle line:84%
Forgive you?

02:26:32.300 --> 02:27:12.934 align:middle line:84%
Doctor!

02:27:12.934 --> 02:27:15.458 align:middle line:84%
Mother!

02:27:15.458 --> 02:27:20.250 align:middle line:84%
You didn't die! You were killed!

02:27:20.250 --> 02:27:49.831 align:middle line:90%
That heartless judge has killed you!
To make sure that he isn't exposed!

02:27:49.831 --> 02:28:03.179 align:middle line:84%
Judge sir!

02:28:03.179 --> 02:28:05.323 align:middle line:84%
Judge sir!

02:28:05.323 --> 02:28:11.837 align:middle line:90%
Have you decided the verdict
about the case?

02:28:11.837 --> 02:28:17.627 align:middle line:90%
Case?
- Raj's case.

02:28:17.627 --> 02:28:22.994 align:middle line:90%
You are going mad!
What are you doing to yourself?

02:28:22.994 --> 02:28:26.680 align:middle line:84%
You are a mature, educated woman.

02:28:26.680 --> 02:28:29.846 align:middle line:90%
In a few days, you'll start
going to court as a lawyer.

02:28:29.846 --> 02:28:37.174 align:middle line:90%
You might even make a judge.
If you get emotional over every case...

02:28:37.174 --> 02:28:38.820 align:middle line:90%
..you will never be able to
dispense justice.

02:28:38.820 --> 02:28:46.253 align:middle line:90%
This is not a lawsuit.
It's my life!

02:28:46.253 --> 02:28:51.426 align:middle line:90%
Do you not understand as much?
- Irrespective, it won't alter the law.

02:28:51.426 --> 02:28:53.476 align:middle line:90%
Nor should you let your emotions
come in the way of justice.

02:28:53.476 --> 02:28:57.716 align:middle line:90%
Justice is all I seek.
Raj is completely innocent.

02:28:57.716 --> 02:29:00.491 align:middle line:90%
He killed Jagga tying to save
his mother.

02:29:00.491 --> 02:29:04.244 align:middle line:90%
You can read his mother's
dying declaration.

02:29:04.244 --> 02:29:07.491 align:middle line:90%
In this particular case,
Raj might merit pardon.

02:29:07.491 --> 02:29:11.372 align:middle line:90%
But his whole life is a long story
of involvement with crime and sin.

02:29:11.372 --> 02:29:16.959 align:middle line:90%
I cannot comprehend how you can
sympathise with such a person.

02:29:16.959 --> 02:29:21.234 align:middle line:84%
How can you love him?

02:29:21.234 --> 02:29:31.519 align:middle line:84%
You have studied the law.

02:29:31.519 --> 02:29:37.403 align:middle line:84%
But my heart has not read the laws.

02:29:37.403 --> 02:29:43.396 align:middle line:84%
Heart... and the laws.

02:29:43.396 --> 02:29:49.880 align:middle line:84%
The laws... and the heart.

02:29:49.880 --> 02:29:53.645 align:middle line:84%
What a strange concoction.

02:29:53.645 --> 02:29:57.754 align:middle line:84%
But you are right.

02:29:57.754 --> 02:30:01.756 align:middle line:84%
The heart heeds no laws.

02:30:01.756 --> 02:30:05.821 align:middle line:84%
No laws at all.

02:30:05.821 --> 02:30:26.735 align:middle line:84%
Not even mine.

02:30:26.735 --> 02:30:31.307 align:middle line:90%
No!
- Get out, Rita.

02:30:31.307 --> 02:30:34.936 align:middle line:90%
I'm in a murderous rage!
- Have you gone mad?

02:30:34.936 --> 02:30:38.917 align:middle line:90%
So you have escaped?
- Yes.

02:30:38.917 --> 02:30:40.321 align:middle line:84%
To settle the score with you.

02:30:40.321 --> 02:30:41.156 align:middle line:84%
Raj..

02:30:41.156 --> 02:30:48.260 align:middle line:90%
Then you will be happy to know
that your lawyer...

02:30:48.260 --> 02:30:51.687 align:middle line:90%
...had just convinced me
about your innocence.

02:30:51.687 --> 02:30:55.268 align:middle line:90%
I was inclined to let you off
tomorrow.

02:30:55.268 --> 02:30:57.978 align:middle line:84%
I want no mercy from you.

02:30:57.978 --> 02:31:01.691 align:middle line:90%
I don't want your justice,
your law, nothing!

02:31:01.691 --> 02:31:06.908 align:middle line:84%
All I want...

02:31:06.908 --> 02:31:12.890 align:middle line:90%
Lost your nerve?
You need guts to kill someone.

02:31:12.890 --> 02:31:19.733 align:middle line:90%
You should be thanking the one
who has just saved your life.

02:31:19.733 --> 02:31:22.513 align:middle line:90%
What if I were to use this very knife
to rip your heart out?

02:31:22.513 --> 02:31:25.900 align:middle line:90%
What else can the verdict
of the courts be?

02:31:25.900 --> 02:31:29.630 align:middle line:90%
Judge Raghunath was compelled to kill
a criminal to save his own life.

02:31:29.630 --> 02:31:40.640 align:middle line:90%
Have you gone out of your mind too?
- I was. For a second.

02:31:40.640 --> 02:31:47.120 align:middle line:90%
For the scum that he is,
the hangman's noose will be better.

02:31:47.120 --> 02:31:51.907 align:middle line:84%
Raj. Raj.

02:31:51.907 --> 02:31:55.197 align:middle line:90%
This is the story of
Raj's life and crimes.

02:31:55.197 --> 02:32:00.502 align:middle line:90%
Now you know why and how
he took to crime.

02:32:00.502 --> 02:32:04.892 align:middle line:90%
My Lord, the one who is guilty
is his father...

02:32:04.892 --> 02:32:09.144 align:middle line:90%
..who drove an innocent woman from
his house, and denied his own son.

02:32:09.144 --> 02:32:11.610 align:middle line:90%
He is the one who forced them
to go begging from door to door.

02:32:11.610 --> 02:32:16.228 align:middle line:90%
And in the company of criminals,
he went astray.

02:32:16.228 --> 02:32:18.933 align:middle line:84%
My Lord and members of the Jury...

02:32:18.933 --> 02:32:21.353 align:middle line:90%
..if Raj is to be punished
for his crime..

02:32:21.353 --> 02:32:23.595 align:middle line:90%
..then his father should be
punished too.

02:32:23.595 --> 02:32:27.993 align:middle line:84%
My Lord, I would like to say something.

02:32:27.993 --> 02:32:33.950 align:middle line:90%
Emotion has got the better
of the counsel for defence.

02:32:33.950 --> 02:32:36.803 align:middle line:90%
In her anxiety to save the accused,
the counsel has presented...

02:32:36.803 --> 02:32:42.659 align:middle line:90%
..an interesting story,
however incongruous it might be...

02:32:42.659 --> 02:32:47.928 align:middle line:90%
..to try and prove that
some criminal happens to be my son!

02:32:47.928 --> 02:32:53.110 align:middle line:90%
But I ask, what evidence
does the counsel have?

02:32:53.110 --> 02:32:56.303 align:middle line:90%
No evidence on earth will convince you
that Raj is your son...

02:32:56.303 --> 02:32:59.553 align:middle line:90%
..not unless you are willing
to accept him as your son.

02:32:59.553 --> 02:33:04.898 align:middle line:90%
If there be proof, it lies deep
in your heart and in Raj's eyes.

02:33:04.898 --> 02:33:09.552 align:middle line:90%
Look at him. The same eyes,
the same high brow.

02:33:09.552 --> 02:33:13.654 align:middle line:90%
He even speaks like you speak.
He's just as adamant as you are.

02:33:13.654 --> 02:33:16.223 align:middle line:90%
Are you still not willing
to accept him as your son?

02:33:16.223 --> 02:33:19.739 align:middle line:84%
Ms Rita, the law heeds no emotion.

02:33:19.739 --> 02:33:24.781 align:middle line:90%
Nor my Lord, does the heart
heed any law.

02:33:24.781 --> 02:33:29.786 align:middle line:84%
I have no more to say.

02:33:29.786 --> 02:33:42.435 align:middle line:90%
If the accused has anything to say
in his defence, he may proceed.

02:33:42.435 --> 02:33:49.601 align:middle line:90%
Yes. At last,
after being branded a murderer...

02:33:49.601 --> 02:33:53.278 align:middle line:84%
..I hold your attention.

02:33:53.278 --> 02:34:00.286 align:middle line:90%
Had I been heard earlier, perhaps
I would never have had to stand here.

02:34:00.286 --> 02:34:03.436 align:middle line:90%
Ms Rita has tried her best
to save me from being hanged.

02:34:03.436 --> 02:34:06.582 align:middle line:90%
And not only in this particular case;
in my personal life too.

02:34:06.582 --> 02:34:11.967 align:middle line:90%
In my defence, I wish to say nothing.
I am evil.

02:34:11.967 --> 02:34:14.174 align:middle line:90%
I've been a vagabond ever since
I was a child.

02:34:14.174 --> 02:34:17.550 align:middle line:84%
I'm a murderer, a criminal.

02:34:17.550 --> 02:34:22.383 align:middle line:90%
You may punish me as you please.
But sin, crime, hatred and violence...

02:34:22.383 --> 02:34:25.508 align:middle line:90%
..this vicious circle that holds
your society in a vice-grip...

02:34:25.508 --> 02:34:28.557 align:middle line:90%
..do you think it can be broken
by hanging me?

02:34:28.557 --> 02:34:31.467 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to tell you
the story of my life.

02:34:31.467 --> 02:34:39.360 align:middle line:90%
But all I want to say is, I did not
inherit crime from my parents.

02:34:39.360 --> 02:34:41.383 align:middle line:90%
From that gutter full of filth
that flows beside my shanty...

02:34:41.383 --> 02:34:47.633 align:middle line:90%
...I picked up crime. That gutter
is still flowing over.

02:34:47.633 --> 02:34:52.592 align:middle line:84%
And the virus still breeds.

02:34:52.592 --> 02:34:56.467 align:middle line:90%
And countless children who live
in those slums...

02:34:56.467 --> 02:34:59.202 align:middle line:90%
..are falling prey to the virus
every day.

02:34:59.202 --> 02:35:06.336 align:middle line:90%
Do not think of me. Those children
are the ones you must care for.

02:35:06.336 --> 02:35:09.688 align:middle line:84%
You must care for your children.

02:35:09.688 --> 02:35:13.911 align:middle line:90%
Lest come the day when...
yours...

02:35:13.911 --> 02:35:15.794 align:middle line:84%
..and yours...

02:35:15.794 --> 02:35:19.410 align:middle line:84%
..and yours...

02:35:19.410 --> 02:35:21.505 align:middle line:90%
..and your son too stands
in these docks to reiterate...

02:35:21.505 --> 02:35:26.229 align:middle line:90%
..that it's an honest father's blood
that flows in my veins.

02:35:26.229 --> 02:35:31.313 align:middle line:90%
Time was when I was an innocent boy,
just like your sons.

02:35:31.313 --> 02:35:37.200 align:middle line:90%
Like all mothers, my mother too
wove a golden dream for me.

02:35:37.200 --> 02:35:41.923 align:middle line:90%
She would say, "My son will grow up
to become a lawyer".

02:35:41.923 --> 02:35:50.236 align:middle line:90%
Then he will become a magistrate.
And then, a judge... like his father.

02:35:50.236 --> 02:35:53.650 align:middle line:90%
I know the verdict that this court
is about to give.

02:35:53.650 --> 02:36:00.840 align:middle line:90%
And I'm willing to suffer any sentence.
For my sins, this is atonement.

02:36:00.840 --> 02:36:05.270 align:middle line:90%
But I await the decision
from yet another quarter.

02:36:05.270 --> 02:36:11.957 align:middle line:90%
I want to know Judge Raghunath,
what says your heart?

02:36:11.957 --> 02:36:38.631 align:middle line:84%
What says your heart?

02:36:38.631 --> 02:37:25.548 align:middle line:84%
Raj!

02:37:25.548 --> 02:37:30.954 align:middle line:84%
Has the Judge come to see his convict?

02:37:30.954 --> 02:37:34.590 align:middle line:84%
A father...

02:37:34.590 --> 02:37:37.623 align:middle line:84%
..who is guilty.

02:37:37.623 --> 02:37:39.242 align:middle line:84%
Guilty? You?

02:37:39.242 --> 02:37:41.789 align:middle line:84%
Yes.

02:37:41.789 --> 02:37:46.706 align:middle line:90%
Tomorrow, the law might
pronounce you guilty.

02:37:46.706 --> 02:37:54.110 align:middle line:90%
But in the eyes of God,
I am the one who is guilty.

02:37:54.110 --> 02:37:56.203 align:middle line:84%
Are you weeping?

02:37:56.203 --> 02:38:01.938 align:middle line:90%
Yes, for the father who found his son,
and yet he has lost him.

02:38:01.938 --> 02:38:04.525 align:middle line:90%
For the husband who forced his wife
to become a widow.

02:38:04.525 --> 02:38:07.684 align:middle line:90%
For society, where poverty
breeds crime.

02:38:07.684 --> 02:38:09.681 align:middle line:90%
For the son who is orphaned
though his father is alive.

02:38:09.681 --> 02:38:11.528 align:middle line:90%
For the child who goes through life
looking for someone...

02:38:11.528 --> 02:38:13.314 align:middle line:84%
..who will call him "Son".

02:38:13.314 --> 02:38:17.430 align:middle line:84%
Son.

02:38:17.430 --> 02:38:22.770 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:38:22.770 --> 02:38:55.964 align:middle line:84%
Son!

02:38:55.964 --> 02:39:01.119 align:middle line:90%
Raj, son of Judge Raghunath,
you have been proved guilty...

02:39:01.119 --> 02:39:04.453 align:middle line:90%
..of tying to assassinate
your father, Judge Raghunath.

02:39:04.453 --> 02:39:08.913 align:middle line:90%
But in the light of the strange and
unfortunate circumstances your life...

02:39:08.913 --> 02:39:12.282 align:middle line:90%
..which your counsel Ms Rita
has presented...

02:39:12.282 --> 02:39:53.385 align:middle line:90%
..you are sentenced to only three years
of rigorous imprisonment.

02:39:53.385 --> 02:39:55.778 align:middle line:84%
Crying?

02:39:55.778 --> 02:39:57.784 align:middle line:84%
You silly girl.

02:39:57.784 --> 02:40:00.195 align:middle line:84%
Silly, lawyers never cry.

02:40:00.195 --> 02:40:02.808 align:middle line:90%
At this rate, how are you
going to practice?

02:40:02.808 --> 02:40:09.985 align:middle line:90%
What use is the practice, Raj?
I wasn't able to save you.

02:40:09.985 --> 02:40:16.178 align:middle line:90%
No Rita, this penance
is very important for me.

02:40:16.178 --> 02:40:21.610 align:middle line:90%
Only after I've been through this,
will I be worthy of you.

02:40:21.610 --> 02:40:26.666 align:middle line:90%
With you beside me,
I can go through anything.

02:40:26.666 --> 02:40:29.788 align:middle line:84%
I will become an honest man.

02:40:29.788 --> 02:40:33.219 align:middle line:84%
Everyone will say I'm a good man.

02:40:33.219 --> 02:40:37.661 align:middle line:84%
I will read, I will write.

02:40:37.661 --> 02:40:41.936 align:middle line:90%
And just like Ma used to say,
first I'll become a lawyer...

02:40:41.936 --> 02:40:46.930 align:middle line:84%
..then a magistrate.

02:40:46.930 --> 02:40:50.634 align:middle line:84%
And then, a judge.

02:40:50.634 --> 02:40:58.680 align:middle line:90%
Last night I saw a judge.
And I liked him.

02:40:58.680 --> 02:41:01.878 align:middle line:84%
I'll become a judge.

02:41:01.878 --> 02:41:04.341 align:middle line:90%
You won't call me a savage anymore,
will you?

02:41:04.341 --> 02:41:12.210 align:middle line:84%
I will. You savage!

02:41:12.210 --> 02:41:14.792 align:middle line:84%
Time up.

02:41:14.792 --> 02:41:30.940 align:middle line:84%
Come on.

02:41:30.940 --> 02:41:33.333 align:middle line:84%
Keep this.

02:41:33.333 --> 02:41:37.710 align:middle line:84%
It's your gift.

02:41:37.710 --> 02:41:40.556 align:middle line:84%
Don't worry. I didn't steal it.

02:41:40.556 --> 02:41:42.773 align:middle line:84%
I just smuggled it in.

02:41:42.773 --> 02:41:56.505 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

02:41:56.505 --> 02:42:04.644 align:middle line:90%
Not your fault, Rita.
It's just the way I look.

02:42:04.644 --> 02:42:06.315 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

02:42:06.315 --> 02:42:09.218 align:middle line:84%
Raj.

02:42:09.218 --> 02:42:15.757 align:middle line:90%
Three years isn't too long, Raj.
I'll wait for you.

02:42:15.757 --> 02:42:17.508 align:middle line:84%
Rita.

02:42:17.508 --> 02:42:25.659 align:middle line:90%
I'll wait for you!
- Don't cry.

02:42:25.659 --> 02:42:33.945 align:middle line:84%
Number 308... move it.

02:42:33.945 --> 02:42:52.261 align:middle line:84%
I should be.

02:42:52.261 --> 02:42:55.106 align:middle line:90%
"I'm not flourishing,
I am not ruined."

02:42:55.106 --> 02:42:57.947 align:middle line:84%
"Still I sing happy songs."

02:42:57.947 --> 02:43:02.820 align:middle line:84%
"Still I sing happy songs."

02:43:02.820 --> 02:43:04.889 align:middle line:84%
"My heart is filled with wounds."

02:43:04.889 --> 02:43:10.782 align:middle line:84%
"But still these lively eyes smile."

02:43:10.782 --> 02:43:16.447 align:middle line:84%
"World.."

02:43:16.447 --> 02:43:27.757 align:middle line:90%
"World, I am troubled by your
sorrows or misfortunes."

02:43:27.757 --> 02:43:32.757 align:middle line:84%
"I am a vagabond."